title: Critique of "Terrorism Lite": Mic the Vegan, Glenn Greenwald, etc.
description:
In the 21st century "open rescue" has incorporated some of the worst elements of both internet fame-whoring and terrorism —and I'm opposed to it as a matter of principle (despite all the vegans lining up to make excuses for it as "terrorism lite").  Frankly, the F.B.I. is right on this one.  If you believe in transparent, democratic method, then you do not believe in DxE, and you shouldn't be making excuses for them!

Footnote: the thumbnail image goes with the slogan, "The F.B.I. is right: no excuses for 'Terrorism Lite.'"  I was tempted, instead, to build the title around the concept of "dry snitching", but I think that a very small percentage of my audience would have had any idea what I meant by that (slang) term.  :-/
